+{"id":"frankenpandas-qq7xq","title":"fd90.210: Add read_sql_with_options to prelude","description":"fd90.210: Add read_sql_with_options to the prelude.

Same half-surface pattern as fd90.207 (read_csv_with_options) and fd90.209 (write_sql_with_options):

- read_sql is in the prelude
- SqlReadOptions is in the prelude (added fd90.206)
- BUT read_sql_with_options(&conn, query, &opts) is NOT in the prelude

The README documents SqlReadOptions surface (params, parse_dates, coerce_float, dtype, schema, columns, index_col) and the typical usage pattern is `read_sql_with_options(&conn, sql, &opts)?`.

Scope:
- Add read_sql_with_options to prelude
- Extend prelude_completeness_compile_guard

